Surface Restoration & Modernization: Lakeville, MN Interior

In Lakeville, MN, we took on a high-needs project for Stacy Erickson that required extensive structural surface restoration. The existing walls were unsanded, rough to the touch, and suffered from visible scuffs, dents, and chemical surface damage. We performed an intensive "Mechanical Bond" preparation—sanding the substrate smooth and applying a specialized primer to ensure a flawless foundation for the new finish. The final renewal transitioned the space from a tired, damaged gray to a sophisticated, deep slate blue-gray that adds both calm and character to the home. This project is a prime example of how professional preparation can turn a failing surface into a high-end, durable masterpiece.

